parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission shift control assembly can cause the vehicle to malfunction, preventing the car from being locked, and leading to battery drain. This issue can also cause inconvenience and potentially lead to safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle displays a "shift to park" message on the DIC along with an audible warning
even when the car is already in park. The vehicle will not allow the driver to lock the car
and the battery may drain.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the rear view camera can cause a safety risk, as the driver may not be able to see obstacles behind the vehicle, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The backup grid randomly disappears on the rear view camera when the vehicle is in reverse. This issue occurs frequently
sometimes every time the transmission is shifted into reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the auxiliary pump can cause a loud and annoying noise, which can be distracting and potentially lead to driver fatigue.
symptoms: The auxiliary pump makes an excessively loud noise when the auto start/stop system is engaged
which is not normal operation. The noise is loud enough to be heard from a distance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to complete or confirm recall repairs can lead to ongoing safety risks, as the recalled component or system may still be defective, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Incomplete or unconfirmed recall repairs
lack of documentation or confirmation from the dealership
ongoing safety concerns despite recall notification.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning backup camera display can increase the risk of accidents or injuries, particularly when reversing, as the driver may not have a clear view of the surroundings.
symptoms: Backup camera display does not work properly
grid lines do not appear
warning messages do not display
camera display only shows a live feed without additional safety features.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loud humming noise from the transmission can be a sign of a failing transmission component, which can lead to premature wear, reduced fuel efficiency, and potentially cause the transmission to fail, leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loud humming noise when shifting gears
noise near the engine
loud humming noise when slowing down to 5 mph.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The leakage of fluid from the rear differential can cause the differential to overheat, leading to premature wear, reduced traction, and potentially cause the differential to fail, affecting vehicle stability and control.
symptoms: Fluid leaking onto the garage floor
rear differential pinion seal failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to fail to stop or slow down, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle does not stop or slow down when the brake pedal is depressed
especially during panic stops or in wet road conditions.

symptoms: The vehicle does not stop or slow down when the brake pedal is depressed

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The use of double-sided tape to attach side skirts can lead to detachment while driving, causing cosmetic damage, and potentially obstructing the driver's view or creating a hazard on the road.
symptoms: Side skirts become loose or detached
double-sided tape loses its adhesion
side skirts fall off while driving
exposed edges or rough surfaces.
